                  </hi>. I live in George-yard, Drury-lane, and am in the ser-vice of Mr. Abbott. I boarded the prisoner from the 26th till the 28th of May—he left me, and I found him on the 29th at a livery stable in the Strand—I gave him in charge for obtaining money under false pretences—He was searched, and a duplicate found on him, which led me to Mr. Flem-ing's where I found this handkerchief, which is mine, and corresponds with the duplicate.</p>
